  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#1878 motivated me to think whether `shard_head_root` in `AttestationData` is necessary. \r\n\r\nTo accept an `attestation`, the node must has seen the `ShardTransition` that corresponds to the `shard_transition_root`. With the seen `ShardTransition`, the node can get the `shard_head_root` via `shard_transition.shard_data_roots[len(shard_transition.shard_data_roots) - 1]`\r\n\r\nI think it's a nice saving of 32bytes since attestations are the most frequent objects that propagate in the network",
