    "body": "I may have confused myself. Looks like `shard_transition.shard_data_roots` are used for dual purposes:\r\n\r\n1.) To construct body root for `ShardBlockHeader` in `apply_shard_transition`\r\n```python\r\n # Reconstruct shard headers\r\nheader = ShardBlockHeader(\r\n          ...\r\n          body_root=transition.shard_data_roots[i]\r\n          ...\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\n2.) To verify it's consistent with attestation data's `shard_head_root` \r\n```python\r\nassert attestation.data.shard_head_root == shard_transition.shard_data_roots[\r\n                len(shard_transition.shard_data_roots) - 1\r\n            ]\r\n```\r\n\r\nDoes that mean one of them is incorrect? (perhaps 2?) ",
